{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 discussion thread: https://forum.cockos.com/showthread.php?t=274257\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 mccrabney scripts - MIDI editing from the main screen, inspired by grid-editing in JJOS 128XL, a third party OS for the MPC1000/2500 sequencers.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 the goal of these scripts is to spend less time in the MIDI editor.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 start with "mccrabney_MIDI edit - show notes, under mouse and last-received" this will give a readout of notes under the mouse cursor in Arrange, including the last MIDI note currently received by your controller.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 the select/copy scripts will operate most predictably using these MIDI editor settings:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 -- One MIDI editor per track/project -- Open all MIDI in the track/project -- media item selection is linked to visibility OFF -- selection is linked to editability OFF -- Make secondary items editable by default\par}
